article.headline: Columbia 66, Stony Brook 46
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- John Baumann scored 21 points and Columbia took advantage of Stony Brook's poor shooting to rout the Seawolves 66-46 on Saturday. Ben Nwachukwu added 10 points for the Lions (2-4). Nick Carter led Stony Brook (0-5) with 13 points. The Seawolves were 5-of-35 (14.3 percent) from the field in the second half and 15-of-61 (24.6 percent) overall.
